{
  "page": "Elissa Farman",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\"><table style=\"width:100%\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:left;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\"><img alt=\"House Farman.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/50px-House_Farman.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/75px-House_Farman.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/100px-House_Farman.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:middle;text-align:center;padding:0px 7px 5px 7px\"><span style=\"font-size:80%;font-weight:normal\"> Captain</span><br />Elissa Farman</td><td style=\"border:none;vertical-align:top;text-align:right;width:50px\"><a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\"><img alt=\"House Farman.svg\" src=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/50px-House_Farman.svg.png\" width=\"50\" height=\"55\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/75px-House_Farman.svg.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/1/1f/House_Farman.svg/100px-House_Farman.svg.png 2x\" /></a></td></tr></tbody></table></th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Elissa Farman by Doug Wheatley.jpg\" src=\"/images/thumb/0/05/Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg/350px-Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"682\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/0/05/Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg/525px-Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/0/05/Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg/700px-Elissa_Farman_by_Doug_Wheatley.jpg 2x\" /></a><div>Elissa Farman, as depicted by Douglas Wheatley in <i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Aliases</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Alys Westhill<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Lady Westhill<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Titles</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li>Lady<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Captain of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Fancy\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Fancy\">Maiden's Fancy</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li><li>Captain of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sun_Chaser\" title=\"Sun Chaser\">Sun Chaser</a></i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul></div></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Allegiance</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\">House Farman</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Culture</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">Westermen</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_29_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">29&#160;AC</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-ages_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ages-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nLord <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq Farman</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Lover</th><td>\nQueen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Rise_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"The Rise of the Dragon\">The Rise of the Dragon</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Elissa Farman</b> was a noblewoman of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\">House Farman</a> and the daughter of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq Farman</a> during the reign of King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance_and_Character\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance and Character</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Family\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Family</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance_and_Character\">Appearance and Character</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elissa_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance and Character\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\" style=\"font-style: italic;padding-left: 1.6em;margin-bottom: 0.5em;\">See also: <a href=\"/index.php/Category:Images_of_Elissa_Farman\" title=\"Category:Images of Elissa Farman\">Images of Elissa Farman</a></div>\n<p>Elissa had blue eyes and long flaxen hair,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> and she was high-spirited.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Archmaester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Archmaester\">Archmaester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a> describes her as \"sharp of wit and sharper of tongue.\" Elissa loved <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Hawk\" title=\"Hawk\">hawks</a>. She was a fine singer and a skilled archer, but her great love was sailing.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elissa_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/22/Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png/350px-Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"309\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/22/Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png/525px-Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/22/Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png/700px-Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Rhaena_targaryen_and_elissa_farman_by_chillyravenart.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> and Elissa, by Chillyravenart ©</div></div></div>\n<p>The daughter of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq Farman</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a>, Elissa had two brothers: <a href=\"/index.php/Franklyn_Farman\" title=\"Franklyn Farman\">Franklyn</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Androw_Farman\" title=\"Androw Farman\">Androw</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_year_of_the_three_brides_-_49_ac.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> As a child, it was said that she spent more time at sea than upon the land. She sailed her own boat around Fair Isle at the age of fourteen. By twenty, she had voyaged as far north as <a href=\"/index.php/Bear_Island\" title=\"Bear Island\">Bear Island</a> and as far south as the <a href=\"/index.php/Arbor\" title=\"Arbor\">Arbor</a>. Elissa was betrothed twice, once at twelve and once at sixteen, but she scared off both boys.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Thus, it came as little surprise that she became a close confidant to Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtrotd61.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtrotd61.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/31/The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg/350px-The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/31/The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg/525px-The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/31/The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg/700px-The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:The_Four-Headed_Beast_by_Warp_Speed.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>The <a href=\"/index.php/Four-Headed_Beast\" title=\"Four-Headed Beast\">Four-Headed Beast</a>: <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, Elissa Farman, <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha Stokeworth</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Alayne_Royce\" title=\"Alayne Royce\">Alayne Royce</a>, by Warp Speed ©</div></div></div>\n<p>Elissa attended the <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Rhaena_Targaryen_and_Androw_Farman\" title=\"Wedding of Rhaena Targaryen and Androw Farman\">wedding</a> of her brother Androw to Queen Rhaena on Fair Isle in <a href=\"/index.php/49_AC\" title=\"49 AC\">49&#160;AC</a>. Elissa quickly grew close to the queen, as well as Rhaena's old friends <a href=\"/index.php/Alayne_Royce\" title=\"Alayne Royce\">Alayne Royce</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Stokeworth\" title=\"Samantha Stokeworth\">Samantha Stokeworth</a>. Her brother Franklyn dubbed the four friends \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Four-Headed_Beast\" title=\"Four-Headed Beast\">Four-Headed Beast</a>\", and the friends often rode the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Dreamfyre\" title=\"Dreamfyre\">Dreamfyre</a> together. Lord Farman's <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">maester</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Smike\" title=\"Smike\">Smike</a>, speculated that the queen had only married Androw not because she loved him, but instead because of her love for Elissa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Marq died in <a href=\"/index.php/50_AC\" title=\"50 AC\">50&#160;AC</a>, Franklyn became <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lord</a> and ordered Rhaena, the so-called \"Queen in the West\", to leave Fair Isle, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonrider</a> departing for <a href=\"/index.php/Casterly_Rock\" title=\"Casterly Rock\">Casterly Rock</a>. Though Elissa attempted to leave as well, Franklyn confronted her at the dock and commanded she stay on Fair Isle to be wed. Elissa spat defiance at Lord Franklyn before he and his men were overwhelmed, with Rhaena's companions then sailing with Elissa on her ship, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Maiden%27s_Fancy\" title=\"Maiden&#39;s Fancy\">Maiden's Fancy</a></i>, for <a href=\"/index.php/Lannisport\" title=\"Lannisport\">Lannisport</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Realizing that most lords wanted to take advantage of her or were afraid of her, Rhaena and her friends briefly stayed at Casterly Rock, <a href=\"/index.php/Ashemark\" title=\"Ashemark\">Ashemark</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Castamere\" title=\"Castamere\">Castamere</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Golden_Tooth\" title=\"Golden Tooth\">Golden Tooth</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Wayfarer%27s_Rest\" title=\"Wayfarer&#39;s Rest\">Wayfarer's Rest</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Pinkmaiden_Castle\" title=\"Pinkmaiden Castle\">Pinkmaiden Castle</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_time_of_testing_-_the_realm_remade.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Elissa remained with Rhaena after she established her court on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. She quickly warmed to Rhaena's daughter, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Aerea_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerea Targaryen\">Aerea</a>, as both were unhappy with their lives at the island fortress. Elissa often spoke of returning to the western seas with the young princess. As Elissa was denied the incomes of Fair Isle by Lord Franklyn, she petitioned Rhaena for gold sufficient to build a ship at <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a> that could sail the Sunset Sea. Rhaena denied her request, and a rift thus opened in Elissa and Rhaena's relationship.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/54_AC\" title=\"54 AC\">54&#160;AC</a>, Elissa petitioned Rhaena to leave once more. Rhaena permitted her request stone-faced, while Aerea wept for Elissa. Neither Targaryen princess knew of Elissa's destination, and she discreetly stole three <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">dragon eggs</a> from the Dragonstone hatcheries. She departed for Driftmark, where she took ship to <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a> and made her way overland to <a href=\"/index.php/Braavos\" title=\"Braavos\">Braavos</a> under the name <b>Alys Westhill</b> and secured an audience with the <a href=\"/index.php/Sealord_of_Braavos\" title=\"Sealord of Braavos\">Sealord of Braavos</a>, selling him the eggs. With the gold, Elissa financed the building of her carrack, the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sun_Chaser\" title=\"Sun Chaser\">Sun Chaser</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> She set sail with a word of caution from the Sealord, due to the scandal that the theft of the dragon eggs had caused the Targaryens.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> Androw fell into depression at Dragonstone, as Elissa had been his closest friend.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabbirth.2C_death.2C_and_betrayal_under_king_jaehaerys_i.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>, was sent to Braavos to investigate the missing dragon eggs. The Sealord denied having them, but agreed to reduce the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>'s debts to the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Bank_of_Braavos\" title=\"Iron Bank of Braavos\">Iron Bank of Braavos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Oldtown\" title=\"Oldtown\">Oldtown</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/56_AC\" title=\"56 AC\">56&#160;AC</a>, Elissa searched for a crew for her ship for her voyage across the Sunset Sea, as she had believed since childhood that undiscovered lands existed west of <a href=\"/index.php/Westeros\" title=\"Westeros\">Westeros</a>. Words of her efforts reached Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Donnel_Hightower\" title=\"Donnel Hightower\">Donnel Hightower</a>, and his grandsons, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_Hightower\" title=\"Eustace Hightower\">Eustace</a> and Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Norman_Hightower\" title=\"Norman Hightower\">Norman</a>, pledged their ships, <i><a href=\"/index.php/Lady_Meredith\" title=\"Lady Meredith\">Lady Meredith</a></i> and <i><a href=\"/index.php/Autumn_Moon\" title=\"Autumn Moon\">Autumn Moon</a></i>, to her voyage. King Jaehaerys ordered Donnel to take Elissa into custody, but Elissa's three swift ships evaded the twelve pursuers sent by Lord Hightower.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When he returned to Oldtown on <i>Lady Meredith</i> in <a href=\"/index.php/59_AC\" title=\"59 AC\">59&#160;AC</a>, Eustace Hightower explained that they had sailed south by southwest years ago but lost Norman and his <i>Autumn Moon</i> to a storm. Elissa's crew towed <i>Lady Meredith</i> to three exotic islands, which she named <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon,_Rhaenys,_and_Visenya_(islands)\" title=\"Aegon, Rhaenys, and Visenya (islands)\">Aegon, Rhaenys, and Visenya</a>. Despite the protests of Eustace, Elissa continued westward on <i>Sun Chaser</i> and was never seen again.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Many years later, during his second great voyage on <i><a href=\"/index.php/Sea_Snake\" title=\"Sea Snake\">Sea Snake</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Corlys_Velaryon\" title=\"Corlys Velaryon\">Corlys Velaryon</a> believed he saw the old, weathered <i>Sun Chaser</i> in <a href=\"/index.php/Asshai\" title=\"Asshai\">Asshai</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_long_reign_-_jaehaerys_and_alysanne:_policy.2C_progeny.2C_and_pain.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It is therefore possible that Elissa reached <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a> by sailing west from Westeros.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elissa_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">The queen</a> found her true love on <a href=\"/index.php/Fair_Isle\" title=\"Fair Isle\">Fair Isle</a>, not with <a href=\"/index.php/Androw_Farman\" title=\"Androw Farman\">Androw</a>, but with his sister, Lady Elissa.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfaba_surfeit_of_rulers.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Smike\" title=\"Smike\">Smike</a> to the <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Her dreams were full of sundering rivers and windswept plains and towering mountains with their shoulders in the clouds, of green islands verdant in the sun, of strange beasts no man had tamed and queer fruits no man had tasted, of golden cities shining underneath strange stars.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Family\">Family</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Elissa_Farman&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Family\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div style=\"overflow:auto;\"><table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:separate;font: 90% sans-serif;\">\n<tbody><tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Lord <a href=\"/index.php/House_Farman\" title=\"House Farman\">Farman</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr>\n<tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black;\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black;border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black;\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:2em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:1em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr>\n<tr align=\"center\"><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Eldest<br />son</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\"><a href=\"/index.php/Marq_Farman\" title=\"Marq Farman\">Marq</a></td><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:2em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td colspan=\"6\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"border: 2px solid black; padding: 0.2em;&#160;;\">Unknown<br />wife</td><td rowspan=\"2\" colspan=\"2\"><div style=\"width:2em; height:2em;\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif;\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr><tr align=\"center\"><td style=\"border-right:1px solid black\"><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td><td><div style=\"width:1em;height:1em\"><span style=\"font:1px/1px serif\">&#160;</span></div></td></tr>\n<tr align=\"center\"><td rowspan=\"2\" c